    "updated_at": "2016-04-30T17:25:52Z",
    "body": "Is there at least a way to compile electron for windows xp ? Chrome runs just fine on windows xp like many other apps, for good reason. On the other side, we'd have to tell people to throw their working hardware in the trash (because in reality you can't update to windows-7 because of missing driver support)\n\nany chance to get this working ? I am willing to spend some time on this. Would be sad if we tend supporting wasteful software only. Our new generations gonna pay a huge price for this things, assuming there is still something left after us.\ng \n"
