    "created_at": "2016-05-01T18:01:06Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-05-01T18:01:06Z",
    "body": "You can absolutely fork electron and make the chrome parts of it compatible for XP - those are things like the Touch APIs which XP doesn't support. A number of people and organizations have done it already.  Be warned that CEF is also dropping support for XP (it's really chrome dropping support)\n\nHowever, supporting XP users comes with very significant security considerations, and there is a great deal of engineering overhead in doing so. \n\nTLDR it's OSS you can do what you want, but should you?\n"
  },
